50|$|<b>Mascarpone</b> is milky-white {{in color}} and is easy to spread. It is used in various Lombardy dishes, and is {{considered}} a specialty in the region. It {{is one of the}} main ingredients in the modern Italian dessert known as tiramisu, and is sometimes used instead of butter or Parmesan cheese to thicken and enrich risotto. <b>Mascarpone</b> is also used to produce Italian cheesecakes.|$|E
